<TEXT>
former white house political director lyn 
nofziger expects his conviction and 90day prison sentence for 
illegal lobbying to be reversed saying the prosecutor made 
mountains out of molehills and lied 
i am an honorable man nofziger told us district judge 
thomas a flannery who also fined him 30000 on friday like 
other honorable people i have gone through life making mistakes 
doing stupid things but i am not a criminal 
he said independent counsel james c mckay was not an 
honorable man 
nofziger a longtime associate of president reagan shook hands 
with friends and kissed his wife and other family members after the 
sentence was pronounced 
but he reacted angrily when a reporter asked how he felt about 
the sentence calling the question stupid how do you think i 
feel what do you want me to do say i feel great he asked 
reagan and his wife nancy issued a statement from their 
vacation home in california lyn nofziger is a dear friend of 
many years and our prayers are with him 
nofziger 63 said he would not ask reagan for a pardon because 
he was confident the conviction would be overturned on appeal 
flannery delayed imposition of the prison term and fine until the 
appeal is completed 
i thought things were going to go better than they went 
said nofziger expressing surprise at the sentence his lawyers had 
asked that he only be put on probation 
in my heart of hearts i dont believe im going to serve time 
because i dont believe a prison sentence is justified even if i 
were guilty and i repeat that i am not guilty he said 
still nofziger said i do have remorse i am distressed 
beyond measure i trusted in others rather than relying on myself 
i am distressed if i have embarrassed my family and my friends and 
my president 
nofziger charged that prosecutor mckay set out to get me 
because i would not knuckle under because i would not cop a plea 
and because i would not say i was remorseful and i think he 
succeeded 
he makes mountains out of molehills he has exaggerated he 
has misstated and i think he has lied i dont think he is an 
honorable man 
mckay made no statement during the 25minute sentencing hearing 
but in a court filing last week he recommended imprisonment 
contending that nofziger deliberately flouted the ethics law and 
showed no remorse 
there will be some bitterness but were very satisfied with 
what judge flannery has done today mckay said after the 
sentencing 
nofziger was convicted feb 11 of three counts of illegally 
lobbying thenpresidential counselor edwin meese iii and other 
white house aides on behalf of the scandalridden wedtech corp a 
marine engineers union and the manufacturer of the air force a10 
antitank plane 
the contacts were deemed illegal because they occurred within a 
year of nofzigers departure from the white house staff in early 
1982 
flannery imposed the maximum fine but the prison term was far 
lighter than the maximum of two years on each conviction he 
sentenced nofziger to terms of two to eight months for each of the 
three counts but suspended all but 30 days of each to be served 
consecutively he also ordered that nofziger be placed on two years 
probation 
e lawrence barcella one of nofzigers lawyers disputed the 
prosecutions contention that the former white house aide exploited 
his government connections to enrich himself 
mckay in calling for the maximum sentence and fine argued that 
nofziger unjustly enriched himself quoting a presentence report 
as saying nofziger is currently worth 28 million 
nofziger said the figure was inaccurate and told reporters his 
net worth was none of your business 
