<TEXT>
opec oil ministers opened talks here 
today on possible ways to reverse a worldwide slump in oil prices 
sources said a consensus was emerging that the cartel should not 
respond by cutting production 
although the price depression is costing opec at least 35 
million a day most of the ministers feel that further cuts in opec 
production will not help said cartel sources who spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
they said the ministers instead would likely renew a call for 
production restraint by independent oil producing nations such 
mexico and china 
the ministers were not empowered to make opec policy decisions 
but they hoped to recommend to their cartel partners on what if 
any action should be taken at the next full opec conference set 
for june 
those attending the closeddoor meeting represented saudi 
arabia venezuela nigeria indonesia and algeria and reflected a 
crosssection of views within the organization 
arturo hernandez grisanti the oil minister of venezuela told 
reporters no decisions had been made 
some analysts believe that if opec decides not to reduce its 
production further oil prices will fall in coming weeks because of 
a global glut 
pierre terzian editor of petrostrategies an oil trade 
publication said today in vienna that he thought opec inaction 
would drive the price down by as much as 150 a barrel to about 
14 a barrel for topgrade crudes 
on friday world oil markets were calm the price of brent crude 
from the north sea traded in london for may delivery at 1560 a 
barrel down 10 cents from thursday 
theres a high degree of skepticism among traders regarding 
the outcome of this meeting said peter gignoux an analyst in 
london for the investment firm of shearson lehman brothers 
the talks by the organization of petroleum exporting countries 
opened amid renewed signs that saudi arabia opecs most 
influential member was growing impatient with the failure of some 
members to strictly abide by the cartels rules 
king fahd was quoted friday by the official saudi press agency 
as saying he regretted that some opec members whom he did not 
identify were unsettling the oil market by offering price 
discounts in violation of opec statutes 
fahd was said to have denied recent reports that his kingdom was 
offering price discounts to some customers 
the venezuelan oil minister arturo hernandez grisanti said it 
should be viewed as a routine session of the cartels 
pricemonitoring committee which is authorized to meet whenever 
oil prices fall substantially below opecs target of 18 
it was the first meeting of the committee since last decembers 
full opec conference in which the cartel decided to maintain at 
least through june its existing oil production quotas for all 
members except iraq 
the iraqis have refused to cooperate in limiting output 
analysts say opec has been producing near its 12nation 
production ceiling of 1506 million barrels a day prices 
nonetheless have dropped to between 15 and 16 a barrel 
with opecs production including that of iraq apparently 
running at between 175 million and 18 million barrels daily the 
price decline is costing opec as a group at least 35 million a day 
