opportunity to tilt a settlement in the arabs favor shultz told 
him the united states would not let that happen 
but shamir held fast to his position even though shimon peres 
the israeli foreign minister called negotiations within the 
framework of a peace conference the only hope in town 
otherwise peres warned the outlook in the region was bleak 
shamirs apprehension and husseins approval of a public policy 
statement that implied criticism of shultzs position reflect the 
mistrust that hung over the fiveday mission like a dark cloud 
shamir and other skeptical israelis doubt there is an arab 
partner ready to follow the course taken a decade ago by the late 
egyptian president anwar sadat and make peace with the jewish state 
these israelis are convinced sadat and the late lebanese 
president bashir gemayal who also sought peace with his neighbor 
