the west bank gaza the golan heights and east jerusalem the 
arabs vowed not to negotiate or recognize israel 
in 1974 they declared the plo to be the palestinians sole 
legitimate representative the plo undertook a terrorism campaign 
against israel the united states and moderate palestinians 
the arab positions and a basic resistance to a jewish state in 
the middle east are formidable roadblocks to shultz 
moreover shamir and peres would retain at least part of the 
west bank shultz told the arabs candidly that recovering all of 
the lost territory simply was not in the cards 
and yet shultz said he would not give up 
frequently describing himself as stubborn shultz said he could 
feel it in his bones that the arabs and israelis eventually will 
come around 
whos afraid to struggle against odds he said friday in 
amman you have to be willing to do it what am i saving myself 
for anyway 
ive got a few more months to go here and i want to try to 
leave something constructive for the region and for my successors 
so i am going to put my back into it why not 
