<TEXT>
a court ruled saturday that the government 
may confiscate several million dollars in assets that anwar sadats 
brother and 10 family members were convicted of acquiring through 
corruption 
the court exempted from the takeover several cars and some 
jewelry and real estate but allowed the seizure of bank accounts 
and some property 
esmat sadat brother of the slain egyptian president said he 
would appeal on behalf of himself three of his sons and seven 
other relatives involved in the case 
he said the case was politically motivated and aimed at smearing 
his brothers name and presidential tenure 
the 11 were charged in 1982 a year after anwar sadats 
assassination with amassing millions of dollars through influence 
peddling bribery and other corruption at that time their 
property was sequestered for five years 
they were convicted on 24 counts of influence peddling black 
marketeering and bribery 
the court said that there was no evidence the president was tied 
in any way to illicit activities 
early this month the nations prosecutor general demanded 
confiscation of 82 million worth of property exempting from the 
request a car and an apartment for each defendant 
saturdays court session was for the reading of the verdict 
flanked by two of his sons esmat sadat sat quietly fingering worry 
beads and waited for sayed abdelbaky president of the sevenman 
tribunal to read it 
this is politics this is a public opinion case and i 
expected no less sadat told reporters afterward many others 
were let off without confiscation why us 
esmat sadat went into private business in 1973 during his 
brothers third year as president after 30 years as a bus company 
employee his salary when he left the company was about 100 a 
month 
