the case against three cigarette companies 
accused of liability in the lungcancer death of rose cipollone 
began with a review of 60 years of research into the health effects 
of smoking 
it ended this week with some observers in the federal courtroom 
weeping as mrs cipollones husband antonio gave a tearful 
account of his wifes death 
in between the jury heard expert witnesses discuss cancer mrs 
cipollones 40year smoking addiction her medical condition and 
how cigarettes are advertised and marketed perhaps most damaging 
to the industry was the blitz of secret internal documents obtained 
over years of courtordered pretrial discovery by cipollones 
lawyers 
