their home in central mexico in hopes of getting the statefunded 
surgery they had previously been turned down in texas 
the boy who doctors say can live only a matter of months 
without a transplant was not eligible for aid because he is not a 
legal us resident 
but after news reports of his case a group called the right to 
life committee established a guardianship for him so he could 
qualify 
on friday olsen denied the california childrens services 
request to vacate the guardianship 
the judge ruled that the boy was not a legal resident but he 
also determined that as a ward of a legal guardian who is a 
resident the youth qualifies for the funds 
