iran and iraq reported sporadic attacks 
and shellings saturday in their 7yearold war but both appeared 
to be observing a tacit ceasefire in their missile attacks in the 
war of the cities 
the official iraqi news agency monitored in nicosia said 
iranian artillery shells hit the battered southern port city of 
basra and four other iraqi border towns farther north killing an 
undisclosed number of civilians 
but neither side reported firing or being hit by any longrange 
missiles since friday the missile duel has taken hundreds of lives 
in the past seven weeks 
a military spokesman in baghdad said iraq had refrained from 
bombarding tehran the iranian capital and other iranian cities 
friday while iranians went to the polls to elect a new 270seat 
majlis or parliament 
but he did not say if the iraqi restraint would continue until 
the results of the election will be known sometime next week 
in manama bahrain a navy spokesman announced that us 
warships safely escorted two reflagged kuwaiti oil tankers out of 
the persian gulf in the 23d such convoy this year 
the supertanker middletown and liquefied gas carrier gas 
princess were escorted on the 550mile journey from kuwait to the 
southern strait of hormuz by the guided missile frigates samuel b 
roberts and the john a moore 
the spokesman said the convoy left kuwait april 5 sailed 
through the gulf without incident and passed through the strait of 
hormuz overnight saturday 
iraqs official news agency quoted the military spokesman as 
saying iraq halted its missile and air attacks on iranian cities 
to facilitate some people of goodwill to cast their votes in the 
election 
he said iraq made the decision out of the hope that some good 
and responsible people might be elected to the majlis and work 
toward ending the war in accordance with a united nations 
security council ceasefire resolution passed july 20 
some small iranian opposition groups want a truce in the war 
that began in september 1980 
the last iraqi missile was fired at irans holy city of qom 
south of tehran at 615 am friday iran retaliated by firing 
missiles at baghdad and other iraqi cities but then ceased the 
attacks 
iranian officials have made no comment on iraqs reports but 
they have said repeatedly iran was only retaliating for iraqi 
attacks 
